DATA SOURCES & ATTRIBUTIONS

AgriPulse integrates freely available satellite and meteorological data:

1. **NASA POWER (Meteorology & Solar Radiation)**
   - Provider: NASA Langley Research Center
   - Citation: Stackhouse Jr., P.W., et al. (2018)
   - License: Public domain (no attribution required)
   - https://power.larc.nasa.gov/

2. **Sentinel-2 Satellite Imagery**
   - Provider: European Space Agency (ESA) / Copernicus Programme
   - License: CC BY 4.0 (Creative Commons Attribution 4.0)
   - https://scihub.copernicus.eu/

3. **SMAP Soil Moisture**
   - Provider: NASA SMAP Mission
   - License: Public domain
   - https://smap.jpl.nasa.gov/

4. **NOAA Vegetation Health Index (VHI)**
   - Provider: NOAA Climate Prediction Center
   - License: Public domain
   - https://www.cpc.ncep.noaa.gov/

5. **eNAM Mandi Price Data**
   - Provider: Government of India / Small Farmers Agribusiness Consortium (SFAC)
   - License: Government of India data (public use with attribution)
   - https://enam.gov.in/

6. **CAI - Crop Acreage & Intensity Database**
   - Provider: Indian Agricultural Statistics Division
   - License: Government of India (public use)
   - https://agricultural-statistics.dacnet.nic.in/

7. **Open-Meteo Weather API**
   - Provider: Open-Meteo (Switzerland)
   - License: CC BY 4.0
   - https://open-meteo.com/

